{
    "identity": "nprot-178",
    "title": "Drosophila aconitase activity and reactivation",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "Mitochondrial aconitase activity and reactivation modified for _Drosophila_."
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1)  Sonicate mitochondria four times for 15 seconds in a Branson 450 sonicator in aconitase buffer: 50 mM Tris, 30 mM sodium citrate, 0.5 mM MnCl\n2\n, 0.2 mM NADP, pH 7.3. \r\n\n\n2)  Monitor the conversion of citrate into alpha-ketoglutarate at 340 nm at 25\u00b0C using the coupled reduction of NADP to NADPH by 2 units/ml of isocitrate dehydrogenase in 50 mM Tris, 1 mM cysteine, 1 mM sodium citrate, 0.5 mM MnCl\n2\nat pH 7.4. \r\n\n\n3)  Reactivate aconitase by incubation with 2 mM dithiothreitol and 0.2 mM ferrous ammonium sulfate for 5 min then repeat the enzymatic activity assay."
        }
    ],
